summary: Jon keeps getting elected into these positions of authority and when he doesn't listen to the people who he has authority over...
question: Jon keeps getting elected into these positions of authority and when he doesn't listen to the people who he has authority over it seems that they get some sort of buyer's remorse.  And Jon seems to get these positions because he is Ned Stark's son.  Jon doesn't seem to learn from his mistakes or listens to his people.  A dany stan also said that the leaks didn't say anything about the food.  I think that it will come up in episode 2 or 4 when everything falls apart for dany.
answer: To me on a show like this where characters like Cersei, Sansa and even Dany had to claw their way up, Jon being handed everything and then complaining about the responsibilities leaves a bad taste in my mouth. I don’t mind him being humble but I have no respect for someone who is reluctant to lead. Westeros needs someone with vigor and ambition, not someone who sighs heavily when duty calls.

summary: Catelyn should have left Ned if she couldn't handle being around Jon. Her kids would've been fine, Ned wouldn't abandon them or...
question: Catelyn should have left Ned if she couldn't handle being around Jon. Her kids would've been fine, Ned wouldn't abandon them or pick Jon to rule over them. She just wanted to stay in high standing with a High Lord and took her anger out on a child to avoid confrontation.
answer:
You’re so stupid that you’re hiding behind the anon feature. First of all, women can’t leave their husbands. Divorce is a very scandalous and difficult to acquire affair in Westeros that might fail in the end as it requires the support of the High Septon. Second of all, Catelyn would have to interact with Jon to take her anger out on him. She very very rarely acknowledged him which doesn’t sound like anything you described. Thirdly Catelyn’s father was a great lord, she’s already a person of high standing, she doesn’t need Ned for that.

 Maybe if you read the books or paid more attention to the show, you’d know this but instead you came here to be a dumb fuck in front of everybody.

summary: Who are you looking forward to seeing Sansa interact with? After the leaks and the last two seasons I'm fed up with her family...
question: Who are you looking forward to seeing Sansa interact with? After the leaks and the last two seasons I'm fed up with her family minus Bran. lol I hope there is a Theon/Sansa reunion.
answer:
1. Varys

Varys spent two decades in King’s Landing watching people politick their way to victory or death. I think part of the reason why he was drawn to Daenerys was because she’s not a politician but that ended up being a disadvantage as Dany would rather burn through her enemies than spare them and find a use for them (Randyll Tarly for example). Now I want him to meet Sansa and see exactly what he has been looking for, someone who can lie and manipulate but only does it for the benefit of others rather than themselves. The show did a good job of highlighting the differences in ruling between Dany and Sansa and this will hammer it home.

      2. Theon

The show has been ignoring the trauma Sansa has gone through in Winterfell. Bringing Theon back will not only enhance his storyline because it will be his third return to Winterfell but it will remind the audience that Sansa has survived horrors. Besides it would be nice to have someone who likes Sansa interact with her as she’s bound to have a difficult season.

     3. Cersei

Sansa has dealt with all the boogeymen in her life with the exception of one, Cersei. Since the first episode these two have been intertwined and Olenna’s confession last season adds another layer that would be amazing to explore if or when they meet again.
